“Chicago belongs to the people.” The people, however, have yet to claim control of the country as a whole, or even of the Democratic Party.
Democratic primary voters fancy themselves pundits.
Like most strategic calculations made by Democratic primary voters, it was harebrained.
The one risk primary voters took was going with their hearts and nominating Barack Obama.
But the pundit-voter who thinks of Joe Biden knows one thing for sure: That man is electable.